docs.abstract: “Truth Seekers,” the comedy duo’s first TV collaboration in two decades, is rooted in their own ghost hunting exploits.

docs.lead_paragraph: Simon Pegg and Nick Frost know it’s been a while. Despite being best friends and an acclaimed comic double act in films like “Hot Fuzz” and “Shaun of the Dead,” they have seldom crossed paths, creatively speaking, since 2013’s “The World’s End.” It’s been even longer since they worked together in television — they haven’t co-starred in a series since the British sitcom “Spaced” aired over 20 years ago.
